Build completed: Rails 8 API + Next.js 16 full-stack application

Backend (Rails 8 API mode):
- GraphQL Ruby schema with types, queries, mutations
- Session-based auth (httpOnly cookies)
- Pundit group-based permissions
- Products + Categories CRUD
- Forms engine (FormDefinition, FormSubmission)
- Workflow engine (WorkflowDefinition, WorkflowInstance, TransitionLog)
- Auditable, SoftDeletable, ExternalId, Versionable concerns
- RSpec tests (auth, GraphQL products, models, policies)
- Seeds with admin user, permissions, sample data

Frontend (Next.js 16):
- Apollo Client with session cookies
- Login page with direct Rails auth
- Dashboard, Products, Categories, Forms, Workflows pages
- Dark admin theme (Boilerworks branding)
- GraphQL hooks for all domains
- Sidebar navigation with user dropdown

Infrastructure:
- Docker Compose (api:3001, ui:3002, postgres:5444, redis:6387)
- Dockerfile.dev for both services
- GitHub Actions CI pipeline
- Makefile for common operations
